        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "A -4 Choose r,s,t so that EC = rBC,FA = sCA, GB = 1СВ, and let XYZ denote the area of triangle XYZ. Then (ABE) = [AFE] since the triangles have the same altitude and base. Also (ABE] = (BE/BC) [ABC] = 1 - r, and [ECF] = (EC/BC)(CF /CA) [ABC] = r(1-s) (e.g., by the law of sines). Adding this all up yields",
        "bbox": [
          0.5225563962894494,
          0.24851190455801606,
          0.9210526249442679,
          0.33730158752483475
        ],
