      {
        "id": "docling_exam_paper_en-file-putnam-archive_2001_Solutions_2001s_page_001_8",
        "observed_type": "list_item",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "A-3 By the quadratic formula, if Pm (x) = 0, then x7 = m ‡ 2V 2m + 2, and hence the four roots of Pm are given by S= {Vm ‡ V2}. If Pm factors into two nonconstant polynomials over the integers, then some subset of S consisting of one or two elements form the roots of a polynomial with integer coefficients.",
        "bbox": [
          0.09586466955324184,
          0.5319767443839581,
          0.49072073834746405,
          0.6206395346726964
